Inside the EU/EEE, the first three confirmed cases were reported by France on 24 January 2020 in people returning from Wuhan in the province of Hubei in China.
On 15 March 2020, cases of COVID-19 were detected in each of the 30 EU/EEE countries and the United Kingdom (R.-U.) with, between 31 December 2019 and that date, 39 768 cases and 1 727 deaths, including 17 750 cases and 1 441 deaths for Italy only.
Obtainment of the cumulated number and cumulated incidence in cases of COVID-19
In the European Prevention and Control Centre (CEPCM), the number of cases of COVID-19 reported in each country throughout the world, only received from official sources such as health ministers, national and regional health authorities of different countries and the WHO is updated at 08:00 a.m.
These data were used to evaluate the evolution of the COVID-19 in the EU/EEE and the United Kingdom, and to set a comparison with Italy's experience.
In order to evaluate the prevalence of the active cases of COVID-19, we have calculated the cumulated incidence at 14 days of the cases of COVID-19, taking into account the natural development of the COVID-19, within each EU/EEE and the United Kingdom, for the period of 1 January to 15 March 2020.
We also compared the total number of cases reported in each country to 15 March 2020 to 8 hours to the data from Italy for the period from 31 January to 15 March 2020.
Evolution of the COVID-19 in the EU/EEE countries and the United Kingdom
